1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 9=

3
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:53,820
(Zizhi Tongjian)

4
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:00,380
Come.

5
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:12,420
You're here.

6
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:13,780
Come. Sit.

7
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,300
Here, have a seat.

8
00:02:20,260 --> 00:02:20,700
Sit.

9
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:22,780
So, the question?

10
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:31,940
Thanks.

11
00:02:32,580 --> 00:02:33,180
I'll do it.

12
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:01,940
Get ready.

13
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:17,060
Got it.

14
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:21,540
First question.

15
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:24,260
Regarding the iron wire
golden hook at the beginning,

16
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:25,288
you remember it, right?

17
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:26,222
I remember.

18
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:27,100
The one

19
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:29,100
taken off Zhang Laoba.

20
00:03:29,355 --> 00:03:30,577
Where's the golden hook?

21
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:32,740
It should have been tied to the horse.

22
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:35,420
It was fastened to the stirrup.

23
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:38,060
Can that be used as a weapon?

24
00:03:38,355 --> 00:03:39,666
It can't be used as a weapon,

25
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,400
but it can be used to pick a lock.

26
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:43,260
The golden hook and the iron wire.

27
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:45,288
That makes sense.

28
00:03:45,860 --> 00:03:46,500
Write it down.

29
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,600
Readers will like it.

30
00:03:53,660 --> 00:03:54,060
So,

31
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:56,466
when you were outlining the story,

32
00:03:56,511 --> 00:03:57,533
did you already think

33
00:03:57,577 --> 00:03:59,580
of using
the Long-Range Foreshadowing here?

34
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,300
- No way.
- No way.

35
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:09,060
When you run into a problem,
you solve it.

36
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:10,911
When you get here
and realize there's no key,

37
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:11,890
then you go back earlier

38
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:14,060
and find something
that works like a key.

39
00:04:14,644 --> 00:04:16,700
But what if the iron wire
golden hook wasn't there,

40
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:20,260
and earlier on, you never wrote that it
was fastened to the stirrup?

41
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:20,940
Then what?

42
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,488
Then you change it to something else.

43
00:04:22,980 --> 00:04:24,580
Solutions come from people.

44
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:25,860
You've written so much earlier.

45
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:27,780
Isn't it easy to dig around
and find a prop?

46
00:04:28,377 --> 00:04:29,300
Alright, that's enough.

47
00:04:29,540 --> 00:04:30,540
First question is done.

48
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:31,888
Second one, continue.

49
00:04:31,977 --> 00:04:33,888
- The second is about killing...
- Wait...

50
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,420
Ms. Lin,

51
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,580
could you get us something to eat?

52
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,577
What do you want to eat?

53
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:40,780
No need to order delivery.

54
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,270
Just go to the pastry shop downstairs.

55
00:04:42,288 --> 00:04:43,888
A quick trip saves the delivery fee.

56
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:50,577
Solve the problem.

57
00:04:50,980 --> 00:04:52,620
Don't answer Mr. He's other questions.

58
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,260
He's very busy.

59
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:56,940
The second is

60
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,666
about the enemy who killed his father.

61
00:05:06,820 --> 00:05:07,220
Yan,

62
00:05:07,555 --> 00:05:09,844
you know this industry
is highly competitive,

63
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:10,380
right?

64
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,340
I'm really thinking of you,

65
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:13,777
and that's why I'm asking these.

66
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:15,660
Besides you,

67
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:17,222
has Ms. Lin signed anyone else?

68
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,700
She only manages me personally.

69
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:21,300
Good, that's good.

70
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:22,500
Then I can rest assured.

71
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,060
With your writing,

72
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:25,460
I'd personally manage you, too.

73
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,700
She really treats me well.

74
00:05:27,980 --> 00:05:29,540
Where do you usually stay?

75
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,555
You don't eat delivery
all the time, do you?

76
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:32,822
I stay at an internet cafe.

77
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,580
When it's just me, I order delivery.

78
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:36,700
But when Ms. Lin comes to see me,

79
00:05:36,860 --> 00:05:37,900
she brings me food.

80
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,140
That's good.

81
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:41,580
This kind of mental work

82
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:42,460
takes a lot out of you.

83
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:43,860
Balanced nutrition is important.

84
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,820
(Delivery)

85
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:02,620
When you discuss the story,
is it just the two of you?

86
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:03,755
You talk at your place?

87
00:06:04,466 --> 00:06:05,666
Just the two of you?

88
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:06,180
Yes.

89
00:06:06,311 --> 00:06:07,622
You talk late into the night?

90
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,620
Usually one or two in the morning.

91
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,540
That's too late.

92
00:06:12,866 --> 00:06:14,020
It's bad for your health.

93
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:15,220
You can't stay up all the time.

94
00:06:15,644 --> 00:06:17,266
Don't you have a girlfriend?

95
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:17,900
I...

96
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:20,900
Exactly.

97
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:23,500
So the killer can't be revealed yet.

98
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:25,660
Luckily, we've kept it well hidden.

99
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:27,540
You're back already?

100
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,377
We have to wait for the next batch.

101
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:30,210
They'll bring it up later.

102
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:30,540
Okay.

103
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,666
How's the discussion going?

104
00:06:31,711 --> 00:06:33,490
Second question,
the enemy who killed his father.

105
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,311
The enemy who killed his father. Go on.

106
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:36,940
You can't reveal him this early.

107
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:39,180
If you reveal him now,
won't your story be over?

108
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,377
Don't you think I'm right?

109
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:51,700
Look,

110
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,711
on your character relationship chart,

111
00:06:54,155 --> 00:06:56,140
it says the protagonist
currently has no clues

112
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:57,577
to find the enemy who killed his father.

113
00:06:57,580 --> 00:06:59,900
Even if he could,
with his current level of strength,

114
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:02,060
he couldn't take
on the entire group of villain bosses.

115
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:03,533
Then what should he do?

116
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:04,860
Rely on external help.

117
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,700
What is this you're writing?

118
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:17,740
This part is messy.

119
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:18,100
Look,

120
00:07:18,220 --> 00:07:18,900
what is this?

121
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,620
There's a structural problem.

122
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:22,300
No, I revised it based on what you said.

123
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:24,060
That's not what I meant.

124
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,980
What I mean is,
you can move from here, right?

125
00:07:26,111 --> 00:07:26,980
Then here, you can...

126
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:28,977
Right now, this part
is already repetitive.

127
00:07:29,044 --> 00:07:31,044
It makes people
think something went wrong.

128
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:36,260
♪Yet no one will ever know♪

129
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:41,860
♪For long time♪

130
00:07:46,244 --> 00:07:47,380
In short, he needs to win over

131
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,488
everyone around him
and all available resources.

132
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:50,380
By forming a team,

133
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:51,900
he can achieve his revenge.

134
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:58,260
♪Calling my name in the air♪

135
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:04,220
♪Stay with open arms♪

136
00:08:06,377 --> 00:08:08,180
If you sell this place,
where will you live?

137
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:10,060
I'll rent somewhere.

138
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:17,380
I think you should find a lawyer

139
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:18,340
and ask properly about

140
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:21,400
your seven-million-yuan investment
to Ling Yikai and your company,

141
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,066
what your rights and obligations are,

142
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:25,300
and how to best protect your interests.

143
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:26,860
I will.

144
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:29,020
But the problem now is,

145
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:30,955
this place won't sell for seven million.

146
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:33,060
I estimate around 6.3 to 6.4 million.

147
00:08:33,711 --> 00:08:35,311
I'm still short by 600,000.

148
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:37,177
Then just give him 600,000 less.

149
00:08:39,311 --> 00:08:40,844
I want to borrow 600,000 from you.

150
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:42,740
I'm not exactly rich.

151
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:44,660
I spend all my money on myself.

152
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:49,844
Only when I need to borrow money
do I realize

153
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:51,140
I don't really have many friends.

154
00:08:57,820 --> 00:08:58,380
Fine.

155
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:00,600
I'll transfer it to you later.

156
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:02,340
But I suggest you

157
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:04,220
think it through carefully

158
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:05,460
before you sell this place.

159
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:07,380
The harder it is,

160
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,100
the less you should
leave yourself a way out.

161
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,888
Don't give yourself
the chance to back down.

162
00:09:11,266 --> 00:09:12,977
Then you'll move forward
without hesitation.

163
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:14,822
And it saves you
the time of second-guessing.

164
00:09:15,111 --> 00:09:17,022
Hesitation is the most pointless thing.

165
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:29,180
(Call. Lawyer Bei Wenqi)

166
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:40,620
The number you have dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

167
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,540
Please try again later.

168
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:49,820
By the way, there's one more thing
I'd like to ask you.

169
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:53,620
Your home decor looks pretty good.

170
00:09:54,777 --> 00:09:56,733
Well, I paid for it,
so of course, it looks good.

171
00:09:57,177 --> 00:09:58,733
Can you lend it to me for a few days?

172
00:09:59,377 --> 00:10:00,940
People are coming to view the place.

173
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,620
If the place looks better,

174
00:10:02,688 --> 00:10:04,400
I can raise the price by
fifty to a hundred thousand.

175
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,977
I'll return everything afterward.

176
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:08,260
As expected of you, Zhao Lanxin.

177
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,180
So meticulous.

178
00:10:10,311 --> 00:10:11,900
Do you want me to go talk to Ling Yikai?

179
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:14,180
He should know what you've done for him.

180
00:10:15,260 --> 00:10:16,340
You want to see him

181
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,580
just to show off

182
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:18,660
your importance in his eyes.

183
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,244
I don't need that.

184
00:10:21,066 --> 00:10:22,688
No wonder you don't have friends.

185
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:30,100
Before I move my things in,

186
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:32,700
repaint the walls.

187
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,860
The number you have dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

188
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:44,700
Please try again later.

189
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:54,660
(Call. Lawyer Bei Wenqi's Office)

190
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:57,340
Hello, Lawyer Bei's office.

191
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:59,660
Lawyer Bei is not in right now.
How can I help you?

192
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,755
Has he gotten off work?

193
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,420
Sorry, I'm not sure.

194
00:11:52,700 --> 00:12:00,700
(Are you home? Want to come down
and see my new shoes?)

195
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,100
(Lawyer Bei Wenqi)

196
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,980
(Zhang Yousen)

197
00:12:35,940 --> 00:12:36,340
Hello.

198
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:37,220
Hello.

199
00:12:37,860 --> 00:12:38,780
Your mom

200
00:12:38,900 --> 00:12:40,355
threw your shoes out with the trash.

201
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,533
I picked them up for you.

202
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:42,100
Are you home?

203
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:05,700
(Lawyer Bei Wenqi)

204
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:09,380
Hello.

205
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:11,820
The number you
have dialed is powered off.

206
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:13,260
Please try again later.

207
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:22,620
The number you have dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

208
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:24,540
Please try again later.

209
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:02,088
You're still here.

210
00:14:02,422 --> 00:14:04,250
I was worried
you might not be feeling well.

211
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:09,820
Come on in.

212
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:18,740
Sit there.

213
00:14:19,140 --> 00:14:19,820
Do me a favor.

214
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,300
Do you use Jixian?

215
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:27,500
Yes.

216
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:38,380
Help me sell these shoes.

217
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,220
I'll treat you to a meal with the money.

218
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:43,220
These are all new?

219
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:44,711
None of them has been worn?

220
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:47,620
Only this pair was worn once.

221
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:48,666
The rest are brand new.

222
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:49,740
You can add remarks.

223
00:15:27,380 --> 00:15:28,460
Why didn't you wear them?

224
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:32,300
They were gifts.

225
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,660
Who gave them to you?

226
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:36,660
My boyfriend.

227
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:47,000
You have a boyfriend?

228
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:48,660
Not anymore.

229
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:51,511
Your boyfriend must be rich.

230
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:53,500
I mean your ex.

231
00:15:53,888 --> 00:15:55,866
He bought you so many expensive shoes.

232
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:56,860
Yes, he is rich.

233
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,777
Then, why did you break up?

234
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,377
He's afraid of his wife.

235
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:12,620
I told you before,
I'm not a good person.

236
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,300
Now that you've broken up,

237
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,555
it doesn't matter anymore.

238
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:23,711
How much can these sell for?

239
00:16:25,780 --> 00:16:26,820
On Jixian,

240
00:16:27,140 --> 00:16:28,180
if they all find buyers,

241
00:16:29,044 --> 00:16:30,444
maybe thirty to forty thousand.

242
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,100
Thirty to forty thousand...

243
00:16:33,311 --> 00:16:34,622
Breakup compensation, I guess.

244
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:39,500
Does a guy have to buy
many expensive shoes

245
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:40,980
to be your boyfriend?

246
00:16:41,180 --> 00:16:41,740
No.

247
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,300
I can earn my own money.

248
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:50,666
Then, what does it take
to be your boyfriend?

249
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:54,460
Love me.

250
00:16:54,933 --> 00:16:56,244
What counts as loving you?

251
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,888
Give up everything for me.

252
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,700
You want to say you can, right?

253
00:17:04,266 --> 00:17:06,044
That's because you have nothing yet.

254
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:09,380
I will become the best lawyer.

255
00:17:11,622 --> 00:17:12,866
Then, we'll talk about it later.

256
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:37,740
(New Rising Youth Literary Editor Award,
Ms. Lin Zhanqiao)

257
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:41,180
I got you a new toothbrush and a towel.

258
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:42,860
I don't stay here much,

259
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:44,260
so take care of yourself.

260
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:46,100
If you run into problems,

261
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,600
try to handle them on your own first.

262
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:47,860
Okay.

263
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:49,420
If you really can't, then come to me.

264
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:50,140
Right.

265
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:50,980
Also,

266
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:52,940
a close friend of mine often stays here.

267
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,311
You can go to her if needed.

268
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:55,180
Ms. Lin,

269
00:17:56,580 --> 00:17:57,020
um,

270
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:59,140
is that written by He Han?

271
00:18:00,111 --> 00:18:01,460
That's Shattered Six States.

272
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:02,940
Back in the early planning stage,

273
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:04,180
for things like character notes

274
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:05,020
and the story outline,

275
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:06,260
he wrote several versions.

276
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,044
Can I take a look and learn from them?

277
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:08,580
Sure.

278
00:18:09,620 --> 00:18:10,060
Ms. Lin,

279
00:18:10,244 --> 00:18:11,511
how did you collect so many

280
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:13,820
limited editions and merchandise
of the Phantom Knight?

281
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:14,900
Are you a fan, too?

282
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:18,266
In the online fiction world, everyone
likes the Phantom Knight, right?

283
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:19,460
I think so.

284
00:18:20,780 --> 00:18:21,900
You're in the industry,

285
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,640
and you still don't know
who he really is?

286
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:24,844
Yeah, I don't know.

287
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,220
Back then,
there was no real name system.

288
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,420
Even now, with that,

289
00:18:29,711 --> 00:18:31,780
if an author doesn't want
to reveal their identity,

290
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:33,140
the editor and the company

291
00:18:33,140 --> 00:18:35,155
are still responsible
for keeping it confidential.

292
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:37,740
Do you know
why he stopped writing later?

293
00:18:40,860 --> 00:18:41,340
No.

294
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:47,260
This might interest you more.

295
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:50,020
He Han's documentary footage.

296
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:51,820
When he first became famous,

297
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:54,260
someone wanted to make
a documentary about him,

298
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:55,820
about his life and writing.

299
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:58,300
But he felt it
portrayed him too ideally,

300
00:18:58,300 --> 00:18:59,577
so he didn't allow it to be released.

301
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:00,933
But the footage was kept.

302
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,380
Okay.

303
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:03,620
This is a DVD.

304
00:19:03,620 --> 00:19:04,940
I'll find a player for it.

305
00:19:05,755 --> 00:19:06,880
Where is it? I'll help you.

306
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:09,180
I'll get it.

307
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,244
Let me help you.

308
00:19:12,580 --> 00:19:14,780
Are you fangirling or studying?

309
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:16,620
Mainly studying.

310
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:18,820
Body here, mind elsewhere.

311
00:19:19,888 --> 00:19:22,155
He Han is about
to resume updates in a few days.

312
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:23,700
Gu Yan has to stay number one.

313
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,177
Which side are you on?

314
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,700
He Han probably
wouldn't care about this.

315
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:30,540
You think so?

316
00:19:33,060 --> 00:19:34,100
Do you even need to ask?

317
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:35,700
Once I resume, I'll top the charts.

318
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:36,820
It's not that I care.

319
00:19:36,820 --> 00:19:38,555
It's just
that my capability is the best.

320
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:39,540
That's true.

321
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:41,500
Fan came to see me today.

322
00:19:41,620 --> 00:19:43,860
He asked me to prepare
for some promotional work.

323
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,044
These are a few different
promotional strategies

324
00:19:47,088 --> 00:19:48,100
he suggested.

325
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:48,580
Take a look.

326
00:19:50,755 --> 00:19:51,955
Which one do you want?

327
00:19:57,577 --> 00:19:58,755
Get straight to the point.

328
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:00,410
Do we need to put together
a promotion plan

329
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:02,940
for He Han's comeback?

330
00:20:05,460 --> 00:20:06,020
So expensive?

331
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,980
This is how they make a living.

332
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:10,260
Of course, they need to earn.

333
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:13,620
But I've worked
with them for a long time.

334
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,420
I can get a discount.

335
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,260
I still have that kind of leverage.

336
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:19,444
So tell me, how much of a discount?

337
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:20,460
I'll handle it.

338
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:24,580
Just a token

339
00:20:25,020 --> 00:20:25,900
service fee.

340
00:20:27,140 --> 00:20:29,300
So it really comes down to money.

341
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:32,380
Well, you still have to pay something.

342
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:35,100
How did Lin Zhanqiao handle it before?

343
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,866
How would I know?
I don't deal with that.

344
00:20:37,580 --> 00:20:39,660
I figure once Fan leaves here,

345
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:41,580
he'll turn around
and go to Lin Zhanqiao.

346
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,180
Whatever he earns less from me,

347
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:44,540
he'll find a way

348
00:20:44,540 --> 00:20:46,300
to make it back from her.

349
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,100
Now that you're competing with Gu Yan,

350
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:51,100
he won't miss

351
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,500
this chance to profit off
everyone's emotions.

352
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:57,500
I went to see Mr. Fan today.

353
00:20:58,740 --> 00:21:00,060
I wanted to talk to him

354
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,020
about our upcoming promotion plan.

355
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:04,780
But what surprised me was

356
00:21:04,844 --> 00:21:07,000
that he didn't try to take
advantage of me at all.

357
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:07,620
And

358
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,100
he was unusually generous.

359
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:10,900
This is aged tea.

360
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,820
A friend from the Yunnan
Tea Association gave it to me.

361
00:21:16,220 --> 00:21:16,660
Try it.

362
00:21:18,422 --> 00:21:19,977
I don't really know much about tea.

363
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:22,060
He Han likes tea.
You can save it for him.

364
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:23,620
Still thinking about He Han?

365
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:26,355
Makes sense.

366
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,740
Someone sentimental like you

367
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:30,820
doesn't just let go that easily.

368
00:21:31,580 --> 00:21:32,580
What I mean is,

369
00:21:32,888 --> 00:21:33,740
you're close to him

370
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:35,260
and to his manager.

371
00:21:37,140 --> 00:21:37,900
So,

372
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:39,500
you have your doubts about me?

373
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:42,177
You think I'd use
my position for personal gain?

374
00:21:43,580 --> 00:21:44,300
Between us,

375
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,177
loyalty comes first.

376
00:21:47,060 --> 00:21:48,340
Look, after losing He Han,

377
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:50,820
it wasn't easy for you
to build up Gu Yan.

378
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:52,780
Of course, I support you.

379
00:21:53,220 --> 00:21:53,620
Right.

380
00:21:54,460 --> 00:21:55,820
That's why I came to you

381
00:21:55,820 --> 00:21:57,140
to ask for help.

382
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:59,700
You know our company's
financial situation.

383
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:02,100
And the promotional firms
partnered with Dingqi

384
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:02,980
charge very high fees.

385
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,340
For me,

386
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,060
it's quite difficult.

387
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:08,260
No, don't say any more.

388
00:22:08,980 --> 00:22:09,980
What I believe in

389
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:11,620
is your future

390
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:13,940
and Gu Yan's future.

391
00:22:14,088 --> 00:22:16,260
Leave the communication
with the promo company to me.

392
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:18,540
I'll handle it for you.
We can talk about money later.

393
00:22:18,580 --> 00:22:19,100
No rush.

394
00:22:20,660 --> 00:22:20,940
So,

395
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:23,900
Mr. Fan, you mean...

396
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,060
We're on the same side.

397
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,940
We fight together.

398
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:30,420
If I help you save money,

399
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:32,140
isn't that the same

400
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:33,780
as helping myself save money?

401
00:22:36,420 --> 00:22:37,780
Doesn't it feel strange?

402
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:40,020
All of a sudden,
he's being so attentive.

403
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:43,244
Is it to get back at Dai Shan?

404
00:22:44,022 --> 00:22:44,900
But didn't he already

405
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:46,660
let Dai Shan move into the new place?

406
00:22:49,780 --> 00:22:50,888
To get back at He Han?

407
00:22:53,020 --> 00:22:53,420
No.

408
00:22:54,820 --> 00:22:55,740
He's a grown man.

409
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:56,860
How can he be this petty?

410
00:22:56,940 --> 00:22:57,780
She's his ex-wife,

411
00:22:57,910 --> 00:23:00,333
not his current one.
What's wrong with her dating someone?

412
00:23:00,377 --> 00:23:02,220
Besides, if he's capable,
he should face it openly

413
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:03,300
and compete with Mr. He Han.

414
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:05,488
What's the point of
stabbing someone in the back?

415
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:09,220
But for us,
that's a good thing, isn't it?

416
00:23:22,066 --> 00:23:23,466
What are you trying to say?

417
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:25,220
I mean,

418
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:28,980
Ms. Lin, with He Han
being with Dai Shan,

419
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:31,140
aren't you at all worried about him?

420
00:23:32,060 --> 00:23:34,100
I heard Dai Shan divorced Mr. Fan

421
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:35,820
because she thought

422
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:38,220
he couldn't earn

423
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:39,100
as fast as she spent.

424
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,711
So she went off to find someone richer.

425
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:42,460
Look,

426
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:44,660
now that she's with Mr. He Han,

427
00:23:45,620 --> 00:23:47,140
could it be that she's after his money?

428
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:49,700
She'd better be after He Han's money.

429
00:23:50,555 --> 00:23:51,733
If we're talking about money,

430
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:53,340
He Han does have some.

431
00:23:53,822 --> 00:23:55,511
But if you're talking
about anything else,

432
00:23:55,555 --> 00:23:56,555
he really doesn't.

433
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:57,620
Talent.

434
00:23:57,733 --> 00:23:59,422
For talent, she can just do what you do

435
00:23:59,466 --> 00:24:00,740
and read his novels.

436
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:01,580
Humor.

437
00:24:02,060 --> 00:24:04,460
His humor comes at your expense.

438
00:24:05,580 --> 00:24:07,220
Actually, he's quite nice to people.

439
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:14,420
He's nice to himself.

440
00:24:17,980 --> 00:24:18,900
That's settled.

441
00:24:18,940 --> 00:24:21,088
If you don't show up for a day,
you'll get a 300-yuan penalty.

442
00:24:21,140 --> 00:24:21,660
Deal.

443
00:24:24,580 --> 00:24:27,260
You're competing with the Han.

444
00:24:27,420 --> 00:24:29,180
So what if you win,
and what if you lose?

445
00:24:29,820 --> 00:24:31,220
The key is, if you win,

446
00:24:31,333 --> 00:24:32,711
how much money do you actually get?

447
00:24:32,820 --> 00:24:34,340
It's like when we play games.

448
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,100
We grind all day

449
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:39,460
just to take first
or second place in a zone, right?

450
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,740
This is just another kind of game.

451
00:24:42,060 --> 00:24:43,060
So if I win,

452
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:45,220
it means I've taken the high ground.

453
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:45,980
Got it.

454
00:24:46,340 --> 00:24:47,300
A famous author, huh?

455
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:48,020
Famous

456
00:24:48,533 --> 00:24:49,688
online fiction author.

457
00:24:49,820 --> 00:24:50,860
Isn't that the same?

458
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:52,540
Once you're famous,

459
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:54,540
won't you have even less time
to come back here?

460
00:24:54,822 --> 00:24:56,333
Better if he doesn't come back.

461
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:57,300
Three hundred a day.

462
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,140
That's ten thousand a month.

463
00:24:59,620 --> 00:25:00,900
Three hundred a day

464
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,340
is already being too nice to him.

465
00:25:02,620 --> 00:25:04,140
It should be at least five hundred.

466
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,060
Five hundred a day, okay?

467
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,620
Fine, five hundred a day.

468
00:25:06,688 --> 00:25:07,980
That's fifteen thousand a month.

469
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:09,533
I'll pay twenty thousand.

470
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:10,620
Twenty thousand a month.

471
00:25:10,620 --> 00:25:12,220
I'll still be a shareholder
of this internet cafe, right?

472
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:13,980
Of course. Money talks.

473
00:25:14,220 --> 00:25:14,660
Greet me.

474
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:15,533
Get lost.

475
00:25:21,022 --> 00:25:22,955
Think you're so great
just because you have money?

476
00:25:23,044 --> 00:25:24,355
Don't ever come back again.

477
00:25:37,660 --> 00:25:38,540
(Unlock password)

478
00:25:41,622 --> 00:25:42,460
What are you doing?

479
00:25:42,555 --> 00:25:43,370
(After deleting the character, all your)
There's...

480
00:25:43,380 --> 00:25:43,980
(equipment, silver, coins,)
What are you doing?

481
00:25:43,980 --> 00:25:44,740
(bound vouchers will also be deleted.)
There's no point keeping it!

482
00:25:44,740 --> 00:25:46,060
- Who told you to delete my account?
- There's no point!

483
00:25:46,060 --> 00:25:47,100
Who told you to do that?

484
00:25:47,177 --> 00:25:48,533
- It's useless now!
- What are you doing?

485
00:25:48,577 --> 00:25:49,800
What are you doing?

486
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:50,900
Our situation

487
00:25:51,460 --> 00:25:52,820
has changed now.

488
00:25:53,180 --> 00:25:54,900
But you should also make some changes

489
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:55,780
because of it.

490
00:25:58,820 --> 00:25:59,940
We haven't changed.

491
00:26:00,177 --> 00:26:01,540
You're the one who changed.

492
00:26:02,220 --> 00:26:03,380
You're Gu Yan now,

493
00:26:03,780 --> 00:26:04,940
not Wang Hai anymore.

494
00:26:36,066 --> 00:26:37,300
Given Gu Yan's current situation,

495
00:26:37,355 --> 00:26:38,660
let's arrange it this way for now.

496
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:39,360
Mr. Fan is here.

497
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:40,660
Morning, Mr. Fan.

498
00:26:40,733 --> 00:26:41,340
Morning, Mr. Fan.

499
00:26:41,420 --> 00:26:42,380
You're early, Mr. Fan.

500
00:26:42,580 --> 00:26:43,220
Early?

501
00:26:43,340 --> 00:26:44,460
Doesn't it start at nine?

502
00:26:45,866 --> 00:26:47,330
Those who are here,
go to the meeting room.

503
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:48,977
- Alright.
- We won't wait for anyone else.

504
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:52,340
(Real-time click data)

505
00:26:52,340 --> 00:26:53,540
(Shattered Six States, He Han,
Author Popularity Ranking No. 1)

506
00:26:53,540 --> 00:26:54,980
(Drunk Old Friend, Gu Yan,
Author Popularity Ranking No. 2)

507
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:59,900
(First Day of Comeback)

508
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:14,860
Let's begin.

509
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:17,022
He Han and Gu Yan are both pushing hard.

510
00:27:17,066 --> 00:27:19,210
They want us to allocate
more resources to support them.

511
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:19,660
Yeah.

512
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:20,340
In that case,

513
00:27:20,511 --> 00:27:21,844
our company is stuck in a dilemma.

514
00:27:21,866 --> 00:27:23,550
We don't even know which side to favor.

515
00:27:23,577 --> 00:27:24,644
What dilemma?

516
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:25,980
What's so hard about it?

517
00:27:26,900 --> 00:27:27,860
This is an opportunity.

518
00:27:27,900 --> 00:27:30,333
These two are setting up
a showdown on our platform.

519
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:31,860
Tyson versus Holyfield.

520
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:33,220
Why pick a side?

521
00:27:33,540 --> 00:27:34,980
Just stir things up.

522
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:37,140
The more people buy tickets to watch,

523
00:27:37,620 --> 00:27:39,860
the more it benefits Dingqi.

524
00:27:40,777 --> 00:27:42,300
I'm monitoring things in real time.

525
00:27:42,940 --> 00:27:43,980
Okay, check it again.

526
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:45,555
Check carefully.

527
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:50,133
The data for Shattered
Six States is clearly rising.

528
00:27:50,300 --> 00:27:50,780
Let me see.

529
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:53,260
It really is climbing fast.

530
00:28:02,044 --> 00:28:03,380
After all,
it's been on hiatus for a month.

531
00:28:03,380 --> 00:28:05,022
And now it's back
with ten chapters at once.

532
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:05,920
That's a strong push.

533
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:06,780
At the beginning,

534
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:08,220
should we avoid the spotlight a bit?

535
00:28:08,780 --> 00:28:09,860
We also have extra updates.

536
00:28:11,100 --> 00:28:11,980
At first,

537
00:28:12,140 --> 00:28:13,340
He Han's side

538
00:28:13,488 --> 00:28:15,155
will draw more attention for sure.

539
00:28:15,180 --> 00:28:17,133
After all,
the return of Shattered Six States

540
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,060
is a huge draw.

541
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:19,533
Bring in all the traffic first.

542
00:28:22,260 --> 00:28:24,100
Dingqi said they'd handle the promotion,

543
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:25,320
but there's no sign of it yet.

544
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,060
They said it's flexible coordination,

545
00:28:27,060 --> 00:28:28,733
adjusting based on real-time conditions.

546
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,777
Who's monitoring it?

547
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:30,460
I am.

548
00:28:31,244 --> 00:28:32,600
I'll follow up on it again.

549
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,000
- It's rising again.
- This is just the start.

550
00:28:35,111 --> 00:28:37,044
It'll take at least three days
to see who wins.

551
00:28:37,260 --> 00:28:37,980
It's rising again.

552
00:28:38,622 --> 00:28:40,088
(Drunk Old Friend)
This growth rate is a bit too fast.

553
00:28:40,150 --> 00:28:42,111
With this kind of momentum,
why wait three days?

554
